            <scopecontent>
               <head>Scope and Contents</head>
                                 <p>William Maclure was a geologist, a patron of science and education, and the founder of the New Harmony Working Men&#039;s Institute. This collection contains correspondence between Maclure and Marie D. Fretageot in which they discuss the social experiment at New Harmony, Ind., and the development of its scientific and educational programs.</p>
                                 <p>Arthur E. Bestor, Jr., directed the arrangement, cataloging, and microfilming of the collection in 1952. Many of the letters, edited by Bestor, were published in the <emph render="italic">Indiana Historical Society Publications</emph>, 15:3 (1948).</p>
                        </scopecontent>
            


